But as we saw earlier, it's impossible to have a finite set $A$ where all subsets $B$ of size 4 have $(B - B).ncard = 11$, because for any set $B$ of size 4, $(B - B).ncard \leq 6$.

Therefore, the hypothesis is false, so the implication is true. Therefore, any $c$ is admissible.

